Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.32,0:00:27.00,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Evidence
Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.48,0:00:03.13,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}"Evidence."
Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.13,0:00:06.84,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}No matter how much you deduce or figure out tricks,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.84,0:00:10.40,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}if there's no proof, the criminal can't be caught.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.40,0:00:13.32,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}That said, no matter how well-prepared a criminal is,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.32,0:00:15.86,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}they always leave some evidence behind.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.86,0:00:18.41,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I will never miss it.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.41,0:00:23.24,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Today, let's recall the time I caught the man who murdered a hooligan in a packed train car,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.24,0:00:27.00,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}by playing back "The Hooligan Mystery (Part II)!"
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.08,0:00:48.13,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}If cases were all men,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.13,0:00:49.59,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}then I wonder if the unseen puzzles would be women?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.59,0:00:51.48,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}A locked-room mystery aboard a packed train car...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.48,0:00:52.86,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Who's the lying supporter!?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.87,0:00:54.69,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}He sees the single truth for what it is,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.69,0:00:56.37,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}and looks like a kid but has the mind of an adult!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.37,0:00:59.04,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}His name? Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.20,0:02:28.54,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}We, the Detective Boys, went with Dr. Agasa
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.54,0:02:30.54,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}to watch a soccer game for the first time in ages.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.38,0:02:42.35,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The match was won by our team, the Tōkyō Spirits,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.35,0:02:46.22,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}who defeated Noir Tōkyō, winning the Tōkyō Derby.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.27,0:02:53.06,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The train on the way back was packed with supporters for both teams.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.86,0:03:01.78,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}But when the passengers left,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.78,0:03:05.04,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}a man's body was found, having been murdered.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.04,0:03:06.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.58,0:03:09.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't move this train!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.08,0:03:11.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A man's been stabbed!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.17,0:03:12.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What!?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.33,0:03:17.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Also, please call the ticket control barriers connected to this platform,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.46,0:03:23.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and ask them to check all the tickets from Tōkyō Spirits and Noir Tōkyō supporters trying to leave!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.97,0:03:29.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Stop anyone who has a ticket bought before 5 PM from leaving.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.39,0:03:34.81,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The victim was a fanatic supporter of Noir Tōkyō,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.81,0:03:41.28,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}a proud hooligan who often appeared in the news and TV due to the crimes he committed:
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.28,0:03:43.03,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Kadotake Akano{\rHonorifics - Thoughts\be10}-san{\r\be10}.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.57,0:03:48.08,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}There were three suspects: Hasue Kira{\rHonorifics - Thoughts\be10}-san{\r\be10},
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.87,0:03:51.08,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Mitsuaki Funato{\rHonorifics - Thoughts\be10}-san{\r\be10},
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.79,0:03:54.04,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}and Etsutoshi Ōba{\rHonorifics - Thoughts\be10}-san{\r\be10}.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.58,0:03:59.84,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The only thing we know for sure is that they all rode in a packed train car.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.88,0:04:05.97,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}But that's not enough to conclude anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.97,0:04:09.93,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}There's gotta be something... There's gotta be something more!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.64,0:04:12.56,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Some other clue to solve the case!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.87,0:04:32.46,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Though...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.46,0:04:34.92,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}How come that person...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.92,0:04:35.63,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}That...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.63,0:04:37.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.38,0:04:40.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, where's Haibara{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.17,0:04:42.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She said she was going to the toilet.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.67,0:04:45.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Anyway, how's the match going?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.59,0:04:48.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You were following it through the radio, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.01,0:04:49.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.06,0:04:53.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In the congestion when getting off the train, I think I dropped the radio.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.60,0:04:56.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And I can't find it on the train, nor on the platform.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.52,0:04:59.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Man, you're such a klutz.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.11,0:05:01.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm sure someone must've found it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.20,0:05:10.79,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}We're still 0-0, and the match is now entering injury time.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.79,0:05:14.12,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Oh! Ramus made a splendid pass to the center.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.12,0:05:17.83,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Higo got the ball, and the defenders can't keep up with him!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.83,0:05:22.76,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}It's a decisive moment!\NHigo goes straight for the goal!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.76,0:05:27.97,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Now one-on-one in front of the goal, Higo shoots!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.97,0:05:30.64,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Ahh, he hit the goal post!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.64,0:05:34.85,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Have even the heavens themselves abandoned Higo?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.85,0:05:38.31,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Even so, there's an enormous booing...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.86,0:05:47.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Doesn't Higo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} remind you of someone?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.78,0:05:49.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Noir{\i0} is French for {\i1}black{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.95,0:05:53.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A traitor who abandoned black.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.25,0:05:55.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What are you on about?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.46,0:05:57.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Though, Haibara...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.00,0:06:02.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Higo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} had a reason to leave his team, just like you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.46,0:06:06.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Higo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} has an older brother from a different mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.30,0:06:08.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His name's Rikuo Endō.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.39,0:06:12.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He was a substitute defender in the J-League for Noir until last year.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.81,0:06:15.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of course, this isn't widely known information,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.48,0:06:19.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,since they have different last names, and they've kept it a secret.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.90,0:06:23.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I found out about it two years ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.11,0:06:25.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,when I was in a match during my third year of middle school.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.49,0:06:30.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Higo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and his brother, who'd just signed up for Noir, had come to see the match.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.37,0:06:34.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Higo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} said something to me that day...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.58,0:06:40.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Would you like to join Noir Tōkyō too, and reach the top with us brothers?" {sounds awkward as fuck, but I can't word this decently to save my life}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.96,0:06:52.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,However, this year, Noir Tōkyō told Endō{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} he wasn't allowed to play.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.22,0:06:57.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In other words, the reason they let Endō{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, who didn't even stand out in J-2 into the team...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.68,0:07:01.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,...was merely as bait to lure Higo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.98,0:07:05.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Upon learning of this, Higo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.28,0:07:11.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,signed up for Big Ōsaka, who'd hired the retired Endō{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} as a coach,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.36,0:07:14.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,in order to fulfill their dream of winning the J-1 together.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.83,0:07:19.29,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Higo was knocked down!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.29,0:07:22.00,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}This should be a yellow card...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.00,0:07:24.71,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}But the referee doesn't show a card!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.71,0:07:28.67,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}And even though their forward just suffered a foul...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.67,0:07:31.05,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Listen to the audience's cheering.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.64,0:07:35.14,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Has Higo been forsaken by all who supported him?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.14,0:07:40.60,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Is there no field in Japan where Higo can play?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.19,0:07:43.81,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Hold on...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.81,0:07:46.48,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}If I recall correctly, today's Tōkyō Derby was...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.11,0:07:50.57,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}As I thought...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.86,0:07:53.45,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The killer is the one who lied!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.45,0:07:59.00,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Furthermore, if my reasoning is correct, the killer...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.00,0:08:00.87,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}...should still have the evidence!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.68,0:08:17.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inspector Megure!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.60,0:08:23.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The train car where the crime took place has been moved to the garage...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.27,0:08:28.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And we're almost done inspecting the entrances and exits of the platform.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.15,0:08:31.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then we've done all we can at this station.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.78,0:08:33.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All that's left...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.03,0:08:36.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,...is to invite you three suspects over,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.53,0:08:38.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,so we can record your stories.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.87,0:08:42.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hold on! That's voluntary, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.91,0:08:46.04,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Hasue Kira (24)\NNoir Tōkyō Supporter
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.91,0:08:46.04,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Mitsuaki Funato (33)\NTōkyō Spirits Supporter
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.79,0:08:47.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Gimme a break! I've got to get back to work quickly!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.25,0:08:50.84,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Etsutoshi Ōba (29)\NNoir Tōkyō Supporter
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.25,0:08:50.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Look, couldn't we do this some other day?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.26,0:08:53.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.22,0:09:01.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If we wait too long, the definitive evidence will disappear.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.02,0:09:07.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Or do you have a concrete reason why you need to leave the murder scene as soon as possible?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.15,0:09:08.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Shin'ichi...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.23,0:09:11.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What was that, old man?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.86,0:09:14.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't talk like you're a detective!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.99,0:09:18.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could it be that you figured out who the killer is?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.16,0:09:19.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Uh...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.53,0:09:24.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of course. It became clear when I heard the three's stories.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.66,0:09:28.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The killer is the lying fake supporter!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.38,0:09:29.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Lying?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.79,0:09:31.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Fake supporter?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.63,0:09:33.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of course!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.30,0:09:35.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's this guy, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.34,0:09:36.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.34,0:09:42.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I remember you saying that you missed seeing the two wingers score the winning goal.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.06,0:09:44.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What about it?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.39,0:09:47.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The Hide-Naoki combo scored the winning goal.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.56,0:09:50.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They're forwards who move freely through the field.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.36,0:09:54.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They're not wingers, whose main job is to stay in the lines and recover the ball.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.82,0:09:56.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is this true?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.74,0:09:58.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.53,0:10:01.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Furthermore, wingers are part of an old game tactic.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.53,0:10:04.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's not really used in soccer nowadays.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.66,0:10:09.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, well, I've only been a soccer fan for a short time.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.33,0:10:15.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And I thought I remembered someone saying Hide and Naoki were really good wingers...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.67,0:10:18.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Stop playing dumb!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.30,0:10:20.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're the killer, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.18,0:10:21.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.85,0:10:23.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's just an honest mistake!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.31,0:10:24.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.68,0:10:29.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Referring to them as "wingers" is a mistake, but not a lie.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.81,0:10:32.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then who...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.48,0:10:36.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm talking about the person who didn't watch the game,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.11,0:10:40.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but who acted otherwise.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.82,0:10:43.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, I'm not surprised.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.28,0:10:48.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Today's match was the Tōkyō Derby, between the two greatest teams in Tōkyō.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.92,0:10:51.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The stadium was packed.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.25,0:10:57.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If the killer had watched the game along with Akano{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, who was at the stands,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.34,0:11:02.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,he would surely have lost sight of him among the crowd after the match.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.64,0:11:06.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then where did the killer wait for him?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.10,0:11:09.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Probably inside the stadium's toilet.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.64,0:11:14.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He listened to the match on the radio, and as soon as the match was over,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.90,0:11:18.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,he probably hurried over to the exit, and waited there for Akano{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.07,0:11:22.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But who's this lying killer?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.53,0:11:28.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,May I ask them some questions, to verify if they really {\i1}did{\i} watch the game or not?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.50,0:11:30.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I watched the whole thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.21,0:11:33.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I saw Naoki's shot from the front stand.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.25,0:11:39.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was so annoyed with his shot that I ended up arguing with a nearby Spirits supporter.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.47,0:11:44.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I saw it too, from Noir's supporters' stand behind the goal.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.64,0:11:51.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hide dribbled past all the defenders, and in front of the goal, he passed the ball to Naoki.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.44,0:11:57.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was watching it from the Spirits' stand behind the opposite goal, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.82,0:12:01.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I got that call from work, so I wasn't able to see the goal.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.86,0:12:07.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But you {\i1}did{\i} know that it was Hide and Naoki who scored the goal.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.29,0:12:09.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Obviously!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.16,0:12:14.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After the goal, the supporters around me cheered "Hide and Naoki are the greatest!"
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.88,0:12:19.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you think I'm lying, have a look at my ticket stub, here!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.09,0:12:21.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've got mine too.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.05,0:12:23.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've got mine too, see.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.35,0:12:27.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Either way...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.26,0:12:32.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,For people who didn't watch the match, my explanation might be hard to understand...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.19,0:12:35.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So I'm going to ask these kids who watched the match.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.65,0:12:38.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Where were our seats?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.02,0:12:40.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The front stand.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.15,0:12:43.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's right in the middle, so we could clearly see Hide dribble past four players.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.95,0:12:48.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Though we didn't see this lady in the front stand.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.87,0:12:52.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe my seat was away from yours.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.33,0:12:57.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Whoa, wait. You can't think I'm a liar over just this!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.04,0:12:59.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, no. It's not like that...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.67,0:13:05.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then from what side and which way did Hide cross while dribbling past the four players?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.30,0:13:06.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,From right to left!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.14,0:13:11.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then from your point of view, the Noir goal was to your left, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.85,0:13:13.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, what about it?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.69,0:13:17.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I didn't remember until I saw my own ticket, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.44,0:13:21.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Today's Tōkyō Derby took place in the Spirits' stadium, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.15,0:13:25.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Usually, in the J-League,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.24,0:13:32.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,if you look from the front stand, the home team's supporters sit behind the left goal,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.41,0:13:36.62,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Front stand
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.41,0:13:36.62,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Away
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.41,0:13:36.62,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Home
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.00,0:13:36.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,whereas the away team's supporters sit behind the right goal.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.62,0:13:41.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Meaning that in today's match, the Tōkyō Spirits' seats were on the left,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.84,0:13:45.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,whereas Noir Tōkyō's were on the right.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.63,0:13:49.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now you see what I mean, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.68,0:13:54.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The strange contradiction that the lying killer doesn't understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.44,0:14:05.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Strange contradiction?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.74,0:14:09.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Can you explain it a bit more clearly?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.82,0:14:11.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.03,0:14:12.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Like I was saying earlier...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.78,0:14:15.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you look from the front stand...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.41,0:14:18.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The Tōkyō Spirits were to the left.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.58,0:14:30.55,Signs,,0,0,0,,Noir Tōkyō
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.58,0:14:30.55,Signs,,0,0,0,,Tōkyō Spirits
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.58,0:14:30.55,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Front stand
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.00,0:14:21.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And the Noir Tōkyō supporters were to the right.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.50,0:14:24.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hide dribbled the ball from right to left,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.88,0:14:27.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and Naoki, who received Hide's pass,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.22,0:14:29.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,scored in the left-side goal.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.80,0:14:34.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right in front of the Spirits' supporters.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.60,0:14:36.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In other words...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.56,0:14:42.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's no way you would have said that Hide dribbled past the defenders and "approached"...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.77,0:14:47.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,...if you were sitting in Noir Tōkyō's seats on the right side, Ōba{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.20,0:14:55.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Most likely, you interpreted what you heard over the radio.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.20,0:14:57.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Hide's approaching the goal!"
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.12,0:15:02.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's just wordplay!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.25,0:15:06.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Like him, I just made a mistake. I'm not lying...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.59,0:15:10.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I meant that Hide was approaching the opposite goal!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.47,0:15:12.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I just said it wrong because I was nervous!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.51,0:15:15.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you want, you can check the seat on my ticket!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.72,0:15:18.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You'll see I was sitting in Noir's seats.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.68,0:15:22.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, you weren't there.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.10,0:15:22.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Rather...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.94,0:15:25.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's completely impossible!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.32,0:15:27.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Not if you were dressed like that!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.19,0:15:31.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, hold on. That's...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.86,0:15:35.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Higo's shirt, the one who betrayed Noir!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.33,0:15:39.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you'd gone to Noir's seats dressed like that, you'd have gotten lynched!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.63,0:15:45.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That said, Agasa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r},
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.46,0:15:48.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,this is all circumstancial evidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.17,0:15:50.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We need definitive evidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.01,0:15:53.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He should still have the evidence in his arm.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.59,0:15:58.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You mean the watch mark in his right arm?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.18,0:16:02.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All that proves is that he had his arms crossed in that crowded train.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.94,0:16:04.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I mean his other arm.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.77,0:16:06.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His other arm?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.73,0:16:09.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Think about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.65,0:16:13.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If he pulled a knife out of his bag in a packed train,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.91,0:16:16.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,he would've looked suspicious.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.49,0:16:21.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Therefore, Ōba{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} had his arms crossed while holding the knife,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.66,0:16:24.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,therefore ensuring nobody could see it,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.04,0:16:27.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,as well as allowing him to pull the knife out at any time.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.13,0:16:30.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of course, he had a glove in the hand holding the knife.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.22,0:16:40.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right. And if my reasoning is correct, there should still be something on his left arm. {literally "on his other, non-dominant arm." but seriously, just no.}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.14,0:16:47.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After holding it for so long, the rare design on the knife's scabbard must've left a mark!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.52,0:16:49.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Indeed.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.73,0:16:52.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then... it was you?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.15,0:16:55.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,For my brother's sake...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.86,0:16:59.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I studied soccer, became a supporter,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.66,0:17:02.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and came up with this plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.25,0:17:06.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who'd have known he was the one causing me to fail?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.67,0:17:08.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Your brother?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.67,0:17:11.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My twin brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.42,0:17:15.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A year ago, Akano killed him.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.30,0:17:17.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Killed?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.55,0:17:20.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,On that day, a year ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.76,0:17:23.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My brother came home from watching a Noir Tōkyō match...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.98,0:17:26.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,covered in injuries.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.48,0:17:29.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He said he'd fallen down the stairs in the stadium.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.48,0:17:34.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But that night, he suddenly fell to the ground holding his head,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.43,0:17:36.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and lost consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.28,0:17:38.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He died three days later.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.95,0:17:43.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His death was caused by a brain hemorrhage from a crack to his skull.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.75,0:17:49.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I found out what really happened when I went to the Tōkyō Hooligan site that my brother used to visit,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.71,0:17:51.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Akano's homepage.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.55,0:17:55.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I understood everything after I read his comments for the day.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.17,0:17:59.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Today, after the match, I beat the crap out of a moron who criticised my homepage,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.55,0:18:03.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and threw him down the stairs.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.73,0:18:06.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's what he wrote.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.77,0:18:09.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But how did you know that was your brother?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.48,0:18:11.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, I knew.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.02,0:18:14.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When I met Akano to be sure of what happened,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.90,0:18:19.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,he saw at my face and said, grinning...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.91,0:18:23.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"So you're still alive?"
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.50,0:18:28.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why I decided to avenge my brother,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.67,0:18:30.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,with his most prized possessions.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.83,0:18:33.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then that uniform...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.25,0:18:38.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah. My brother always wore it to Noir games...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.09,0:18:40.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Higo's uniform.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.59,0:18:43.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I never imagined I would get caught over it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.93,0:18:49.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Though, maybe this uniform was...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.10,0:18:53.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,a warning from my brother in the afterlife.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.90,0:19:03.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because if a Noir supporter had seen this uniform and commented about it...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.78,0:19:10.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe it would've brought me to my senses from the thirst for revenge in my heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.21,0:19:12.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"What do you think you're doing?"
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.89,0:19:27.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,By the way, Haibara's taking a long time...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.43,0:19:28.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're right...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.68,0:19:31.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Eh? Haibara's not back yet?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.77,0:19:33.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.02,0:19:34.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah! There she is!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.98,0:19:37.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Look! On the other platform!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.44,0:19:39.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're right...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.90,0:19:42.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's she doing there?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.36,0:19:45.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The train to Beika's on {\i1}this{\i} platform...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.33,0:19:50.21,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Don't tell me she's...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.41,0:19:55.13,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}After all, there's no place for traitors.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.42,0:20:02.76,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}It's his chance to forget everything and escape to a place where the booing won't reach.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.05,0:20:05.60,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}No...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.46,0:20:39.00,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Haibara...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.92,0:20:42.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Haibara!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.47,0:20:48.31,Signs,,0,0,0,,Kanashii hodo kyō no yūhi kirei da ne\N(Today's sunset is so pretty it's sad)
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.91,0:22:12.41,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Haibara...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.08,0:22:15.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Haibara!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.34,0:22:19.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Damn it...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.76,0:22:22.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's all the yelling for?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.97,0:22:26.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You thought I was going to run or something?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.68,0:22:29.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.72,0:22:34.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Here you go, young lady. Try not to drop it again.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.36,0:22:36.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.19,0:22:37.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A radio?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.09,0:22:40.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was looking for the radio that Tsuburaya{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} dropped.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.94,0:22:45.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When I asked a worker, he told me one of the cleaners might've picked it up.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.91,0:22:47.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.23,0:22:55.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You said it, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.61,0:23:00.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Don't run away. Don't run away from fate."
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.09,0:23:06.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You'll protect me, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.02,0:23:08.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.03,0:23:19.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, I'm not some weak girl who needs to be protected all the time like you seem to think.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.95,0:23:23.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, Haibara.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.65,0:23:26.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Higo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} did manage to score the winning goal in the end.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.50,0:23:31.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The stadium went wild calling for Higo.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.79,0:23:40.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Though I pretty much knew it already, but that booing was the motivation he needed to give it his all.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.75,0:23:45.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why are you telling me all of that nonsense?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.22,0:23:47.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm not some soccer nut like you.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.98,0:24:03.47,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Man, she's stubborn...
